    "n_guide_content_mRjCrB": {
      "type": "n_guide-content",
      "name": "t:sections.n_guide-content.name",
      "settings": {
        "use_own_file": true,
        "active": false,
        "must_read": false,
        "heading": "Care & Maintenance",
        "text": "<h2>Care & Maintenance</h2><p>To ensure your Qure Shower Filter works optimally, regular maintenance is important:</p><ul><li>Wipe the filter's surface with a damp cloth to remove soap scum and build-up.</li><li>Avoid harsh chemicals when cleaning, and do not use steel wool, abrasive cleaners, or corrosive liquids.</li><li>Replace the filter every 3 months, or sooner if the water flow slows down.</li><li>Periodically check the connections to ensure there are no leaks.</li></ul>",
        "slides_per_view": ""
      }
    },
    "n_guide_content_mn6QrA": {
      "type": "n_guide-content",
      "name": "t:sections.n_guide-content.name",
      "settings": {
        "use_own_file": true,
        "active": false,
        "must_read": false,
        "heading": "Troubleshooting & Adjustments",
        "text": "<h2>Troubleshooting & Adjustments</h2><p>Having trouble? Don't worry, most issues are quick to solve.</p><h6>Water leaks</h6><p>Check that the shower head is tightly secured, and plumber tape is correctly applied. Add more tape if needed.</p><p>[hr]</p><h6>Odor in the water</h6><p>If you notice any unusual odors, flush the filter by running water through the system for several minutes. Remove and clean or replace the filter as needed.</p><p>[hr]</p><h6>Low or uneven water pressure</h6><p>Low flow can occur for a couple of reasons if the filter is clogged. If the pressure from your Qure Shower Filter feels too low, try these steps:</p><ul><li>Check the washer and flow restrictor: Unscrew the filter from your shower arm and look inside both ends. Some homes have low water pressure already, and the built-in restrictor might be making it worse. You can remove the small black rubber ring with a plastic insert (the flow restrictor) to improve pressure.</li><li>Clean the mesh screen: Sometimes debris from your water supply can clog the filter mesh. Remove and rinse the filter under water or gently scrub it with a toothbrush to remove any impurities.</li><li>Make sure it's fully tightened: A loose connection can cause pressure loss. Reinstall the filter, making sure it's snug but not overtightened.</li></ul>",
        "slides_per_view": ""
      }
    },
    "n_guide_content_JjTLe8": {
      "type": "n_guide-content",
      "name": "t:sections.n_guide-content.name",
      "settings": {
        "use_own_file": true,
        "active": false,
        "must_read": false,
        "heading": "Warranty Information",
        "text": "<h2>Warranty Information</h2><p>We offer a lifetime warranty for the original purchaser, covering defects in materials and workmanship.</p><p>This warranty does not cover misuse, improper care, foreign objects, the filter cartridge, or issues arising from unauthorized components (e.g., malfunctions, reduced performance, or property damage).</p><p>To make a claim, <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:5500/page.shower-filter-online-guide.html#\">contact our customer support</a> via email or live chat.</p><p>Be sure to include your name, proof of purchase, device serial number, and a description of the issue.</p>",
        "slides_per_view": ""
      }
    },
    "n_guide_faq_VCcdx9": {
      "type": "n_guide-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_3Laqmb": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How often should I replace the filter cartridge?",
            "text": "<p>The filter should be replaced every 3 months to ensure optimal performance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_RjHhJ4": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What should I do if the water flow slows down?",
            "text": "<p>If the pressure from your Qure Shower Filter feels too low, try these steps:</p><ul><p>Check the washer and flow restrictor: Unscrew the filter from your shower arm and look inside both ends. Some homes have low water pressure already, and the built-in restrictor might be making it worse. You can remove the small black rubber ring with a plastic insert (the flow restrictor) to improve pressure.</p><p>Clean the mesh screen: Sometimes debris from your water supply can clog the filter mesh. Remove and rinse the filter under water or gently scrub it with a toothbrush to remove any impurities.</p><p>Make sure it's fully tightened: A loose connection can cause pressure loss. Reinstall the filter, making sure it's snug but not overtightened.</p></ul>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_UBDQFH": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is this filter compatible with all showerheads?",
            "text": "<p>The Qure Shower Filter fits most standard showerheads. The filter is not compatible with showers that have built-in or custom fittings that do not feature standard threads.</p>"
          }
        },
